The Kentucky Milk Commission is hereby established and shall consist of the following thirteen (13) members:
The Commissioner or the Commissioner's designee, who shall serve as chair;
Four (4) nonvoting members as follows:
President of the Kentucky Farm Bureau or the president's designee;
Director of the Division of Public Health Protection and Safety, Cabinet for Health and Family Services, or the director's designee;
Director of the University of Kentucky Agriculture Experiment Station or the director's designee; and
A representative of the Kentucky Dairy Development Council (KDDC) designated by the KDDC; and
Eight (8) members appointed by the Governor, who shall be residents of the state. The members shall be as follows:
Two (2) milk producers who are actively and principally engaged in dairy farming in Kentucky;
One (1) milk processor or a designee of the processor;
One (1) retailer;
Two (2) consumers;
One (1) employee representative of a milk marketing agency or dairy cooperative; and
One (1) representative of the Cabinet for Health and Family Services who has experience in the administration of the Special Supplemental Nutrition Program for Women, Infants, and Children.
